## Why physical computing?
- Real-world applications: Physical computing can be used to teach many aspects of computer science, including sensing technologies, feedback and control mechanisms, and methods of prototyping. [Source.](https://doi.org/10.1145/2632320.2632336)
- Learning efficacy: In one [study](https://www.iejee.com/index.php/IEJEE/article/view/1233), students who took lessons in physical computing showed an improved understanding of computational concepts.
- Inclusion and engagement: Using a physical device can help students engage and connect the actions on a screen to their impact in the real world. Plus, according to a BBC survey, female students in particular described feeling more confident after exposure to physical computing.
- Social and emotional learning: Physical computing encourages students to work together, fostering collaboration, interpersonal skills, and active learning. [Source.](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2020/04/physical-computing.pdf)

